devdoc.details: ERC20 token implementation with staking functionality, token exchange, and reward mechanisms

ERC20InsufficientAllowance(address,uint2.details: Indicates a failure with the `spender`’s `allowance`. Used in transfers.

params.allowance: Amount of tokens a `spender` is allowed to operate with.
params.needed: Minimum amount required to perform a transfer.
params.spender: Address that may be allowed to operate on tokens without being their owner.

ERC20InsufficientBalance(address,uint256.details: Indicates an error related to the current `balance` of a `sender`. Used in transfers.

params.balance: Current balance for the interacting account.
params.needed: Minimum amount required to perform a transfer.
params.sender: Address whose tokens are being transferred.

ERC20InvalidApprover(address).details: Indicates a failure with the `approver` of a token to be approved. Used in approvals.

ERC20InvalidReceiver(address).details: Indicates a failure with the token `receiver`. Used in transfers.

params.receiver: Address to which tokens are being transferred.

ERC20InvalidSender(address).details: Indicates a failure with the token `sender`. Used in transfers.

params.sender: Address whose tokens are being transferred.

ERC20InvalidSpender(address).details: Indicates a failure with the `spender` to be approved. Used in approvals.

params.spender: Address that may be allowed to operate on tokens without being their owner.

InsufficientBalance(uint256,uint256).details: Error definitions - Comprehensive error types for precise error handling

Approval(address,address,uint256).details: Emitted when the allowance of a `spender` for an `owner` is set by a call to {approve}. `value` is the new allowance.

Transfer(address,address,uint256).details: Emitted when `value` tokens are moved from one account (`from`) to another (`to`). Note that `value` may be zero.

allowance(address,address).details: Returns the remaining number of tokens that `spender` will be allowed to spend on behalf of `owner` through {transferFrom}. This is zero by default. This value changes when {approve} or {transferFrom} are called.

approve(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-approve}. NOTE: If `value` is the maximum `uint256`, the allowance is not updated on `transferFrom`. This is semantically equivalent to an infinite approval. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

balanceOf(address).details: Returns the value of tokens owned by `account`.

params.amount: Amount of tokens to burn  Requirements: - Contract must not be paused - Amount must be greater than zero - User must have sufficient balance

calculateEarnedTokens(address).details: Calculate unclaimed Fair Reward Token (FR) based on staked amount and time

params.user: User address to calculate earned tokens for

returns._0: Amount of earned FR tokens  Calculation formula: (stakeAmount * timeElapsed * getRate()) / (1 days * 3650000) - Uses time-weighted calculation with rate based on stake amount - Caps timeElapsed at 90 days to prevent excessive reward accumulation - Includes overflow protection for all arithmetic operations

checkIsOwner(address).details: Check if an address is the contract owner

returns._0: Boolean indicating if the address is the owner
Boolean indicating success of the operation

constructor.details: Sets up the Fair Stake Token with reference to the staked token contract

params._stakedToken: Address of the ERC20 token that users will stake to earn rewards  Requirements: - `_owner` must not be the zero address - `_stakedToken` must not be the zero address

decimals().details: Returns the number of decimals used to get its user representation

exchangeFRForToken(address,uint256).details: Exchange FR tokens for other tokens by burning

params.frAmount: Amount of FR tokens to burn

returns._0: Amount of tokens received  Requirements: - Contract must not be paused - Token address must not be zero - FR amount must be greater than zero - Exchange rate must be set (numerator and denominator > 0) - Exchange period must be active (not expired and started) - Requested amount must not exceed available exchange limit  Effects: - Burns FR tokens from user balance - Transfers requested tokens to user - Updates remaining exchange amount

getRate(uint256).details: Calculate stake reward rate based on staked amount

returns._0: Reward rate (ranging from 100 to 500)  Rate calculation rules: - Minimum rate: 100 (when stake amount is small) - Rate increases up to 200 linearly - Above 200, rate increases logarithmically (divided by 10 for each additional unit) - Maximum rate: 500 (caps at the upper limit)

getUserStakeInfo(address).details: Returns complete staking data for a user

params._user: User address to query stake information for

returns.lastClaimed: Timestamp when rewards were last claimed
returns.unstakeRequestAmount: Amount of tokens currently in unstaking process

mintContributorReward(address,uint256,ui.details: Mint Fair Reward Token (FR) as rewards for contributors

params.amount: Amount of FR tokens to mint as reward
params.contributor: Address of the contributor to receive rewards
params.proposalId: ID of the proposal related to this contribution

returns._0: Boolean indicating success of the operation  Requirements: - Caller must be the contract owner - Contract must not be paused - Contributor address must not be zero - Reward amount must be greater than zero - Minting must not exceed maximum supply

name().details: Returns the name of the token.

renounceOwnership().details: Renounce ownership of the contract  Requirements: - Caller must be the current owner

requestUnstake(uint256,uint64).details: Initiates the unstaking process which requires waiting before final withdrawal

params.waitDays: Optional wait period in days (min: 1, max: 60)

returns._0: Boolean indicating success of the operation  Requirements: - Caller must have sufficient staked balance - `amount` must be greater than zero - `waitDays` must be between 1 and 60 (defaults to 30 if 0) - Contract and UNSTAKE module must not be paused  Effects: - Updates user stake and unstake request information - Transfers amount from staked to unstaking state - Automatically mints any pending rewards

setTokenExchangeRate(address,uint88,uint.details: Set exchange rate (as numerator/denominator), max exchange amount and transfer type for a token

params.durationWeeks: Exchange duration in weeks (use 255 for unlimited duration)
params.maxExchangeAmount: Maximum exchange amount for this token (in target token units)
params.rateDenominator: Denominator of the exchange rate, represents the FR token amount factor
params.rateNumerator: Numerator of the exchange rate, represents the target token amount factor
params.tokenAddress: Address of the token to set rate for
params.transferType: Token transfer type (0 for functions returning boolean, 1 for functions with no return value)

returns._0: Boolean indicating success of the operation  Requirements: - Caller must be the contract owner - Token address must not be zero or this contract - Exchange rate must be valid (numerator and denominator > 0) - Max exchange amount must be greater than zero - Transfer type must be 0 or 1 - Duration must be at least 1 week (or 255 for unlimited)

stake(uint256).details: Allows users to stake their tokens in exchange for future rewards

returns._0: Boolean indicating success of the operation  Requirements: - Caller must have approved at least `amount` tokens for transfer - `amount` must be greater than zero - Contract and STAKE module must not be paused  Effects: - Transfers tokens from user to contract - Updates user stake information - Calculates and mints any pending rewards automatically

symbol().details: Returns the symbol of the token, usually a shorter version of the name.

totalSupply().details: Returns the value of tokens in existence.

transfer(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transfer}. Requirements: - `to` cannot be the zero address. - the caller must have a balance of at least `value`.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transferFrom}. Skips emitting an {Approval} event indicating an allowance update. This is not required by the ERC. See {xref-ERC20-_approve-address-address-uint256-bool-}[_approve]. NOTE: Does not update the allowance if the current allowance is the maximum `uint256`. Requirements: - `from` and `to` cannot be the zero address. - `from` must have a balance of at least `value`. - the caller must have allowance for ``from``'s tokens of at least `value`.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfer ownership of the contract to a new account

params._newOwner: Address of the new owner  Requirements: - Caller must be the current owner - `_newOwner` must not be the zero address

unstake().details: Complete unstake after specified wait period

returns._0: Boolean indicating success of the operation  Fee calculation rules: - 0% fee if wait period ≥ 60 days - 0.2% fee per day less than 60 days (e.g., 59 days = 0.2% fee, 58 days = 0.4% fee, etc.)  Requirements: - Contract must not be paused - User must have an active unstake request - Unstake wait period must be completed  Effects: - Calculates and deducts any applicable fee - Updates user stake information - Transfers tokens to user (minus fee)

STAKE_RATE_BASE.details: Base rate for stake reward calculations

pausedModules.details: Mapping to store pause state for each function module

totalStaked.details: Total amount of tokens currently staked

totalUnstaking.details: Total amount of tokens in the unstaking period
